        protected V setValueInternal(V value)
        Sets the value of this entry in the underlying map.

        This method has the same semantics as Map.Entry.setValue(Object). Mutable subclasses can implement Map.Entry.setValue(Object) by calling this method.

        Immutable subclasses can call this method from the builder.

        Parameters:
        value - the value to set
        Returns:
        the old value
